Content:: J. Garland Warren (May 19, 1935 – May 3, 2010) was a Canadian football player who played for the Winnipeg Blue Bombers. He won the Grey Cup with Winnipeg in 1958, 1959, 1961 and 1962.[1] He played college football at the University of North Texas. In 2010, he died, aged 74.[2]  This biographical article relating to Canadian football is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.
